    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The spread of an infection is simulated with a stochastic agent-based model. In a certain range of R0 values, the infection either rapidly comes to halt or a large proportion of the population is infected until herd immunity is achieved. Which of these two possibilities actually occurs is random. The probability of each case is determined \u2018quasi-empirically\u2019. This stochastic phenomenon may explain unexpected infection trajectories.</jats:p>",
